<TITLE> Benapole operations resume </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Benapole, Dec 5 (bdnews24.com)  Benapole land port resumed work on Saturday morning, following suspension of all operations from Thursday morning over a strike in India, officials said. More than 500 goods-laden trucks headed for Bangladesh had been stranded at the Indian land port of Petrapole across the border, according to port officials. Petrapole Clearing and Forwarding Staff Welfare Association general secretary Kartik Chakravarty said passengers had also faced trouble. The Centre of Indian Trade Unions, backed by Communist Party of India (Marxist), enforced a daylong shutdown at Petrapole protesting the death of a transport worker, Animesh, 40, at Bangaon in India. bdne
